 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m989 x2b h2d y288 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">• </div><div class="t me4 x60 h2d y5a ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">17. </div><div class="t m1fe x7e h2d y5fa ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">From what should a person bridle his tongue? </div><div class="t mbe0 x61 h2d y2a3 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1 Peter 3: 10. </div><div class="t me4 x5f h2d y9ac ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">18. </div><div class="t m114 x50 h2d y134c ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What kind of a religion must a person have to </div><div class="t m16d x61 h2d y134d ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">be benefited by it?  James 1 : 27, first part. </div><div class="t me4 x60 h2d ye2 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">19. </div><div class="t m6a2 x50 h2d y303 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What are some of the marks of this kind of re- </div><div class="t m4ab x61 h2d y41d ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ligion ? Verse 27, last part. See note 2. </div><div class="t m5 xb3 h2d y4d6 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m1478 xa6 h2d yebc ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">• </div><div class="t m22d x5f h2d y68 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">20.. How much is embraced in the expression, &quot; un- </div><div class="t mb1 x61 h2d y2a7 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">spotted from the world &quot; ? 1 John 2:15, 16. </div><div class="t m6fb x68 h34 y134e ff4 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NOTES. </div><div class="t ma8f x5f h2d y6f ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. Looking only occasionally into the great mirroi: </div><div class="t mb1b x74 h2d y4ef ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of God&apos;s law, to note how our course of conduct varies </div><div class="t m5f0 x61 h2d y73 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">from its holy requirements, is not</div><div class="t m1074 x8f h2d y1df ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">. </div><div class="t m8e1 x90 h2d y1a8 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> enough. For, like • </div><div class="t mad9 x61 h2d y75 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the man who turns away from the mirror, and soon </div><div class="t m287 x61 h2d y456 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">loses